From Steven D Litvintchouk Subject Re Antihistamine for sleep aid In article A Alice Sanders writes But after you have taken antihistamines for a few nights, doesn't it start to have a paradoxical effect I used to take one every night for allergies and couldn't figure out why I developed bad insomnia Insomnia is a known, but relatively infrequent, side effect of diphenhydramine For most people, this does not occur On the other hand, most people can build up a tolerance to an antihistamine with extended use Allergy sufferers are often switched from one antihistamine to another to avoid this Steven Litvintchouk MITRE Corporation Burlington Road Bedford, MA Fone ARPA UUCP linus sdl